args: Despite her young age, Elisanne was given the\nrank of Grand Paladyn; the leader of all Paladyns.
It is now her duty to demonstrate and\nuphold the ways of the Church in her\nevery word and action.
I have made up my mind, Julietta:\nMy goal should be to unify everyone\nunder the Goddess once more.
I can think of no greater mission as\nGrand Paladyn.
It's a noble goal, to be sureâ€”but the two\nsides are fundamentally opposed.
This may have all started from a difference\nin interpreting scripture, but too much\nblood has been spilled now.
That is precisely why I have to act. It is my\nduty to cast light where darkness preys.

Despite our differences, we are all children
of the Goddess. If I can just earn their
trust, I'm sure there is hope for
reconciliation.
Well, if that's your plan, then you\nhave my support.
Thank you, Julietta. Let us meet with\nthe perditionists then. I wish to speak\nwith Tobias.
Please, at least hear me out!\nYou must know something\nof the Church's history, yes?
Our history is our greatest sinâ€”\nand that is why we must correct it.
We prayed and prayed, and what did we\nsee in return? Naught but conflict and\ndisaster. Why?
The history you tout is a blight\non this religion!
No! If we simply pray together as we\nonce did, the Goddess will guide us\nto prosperity. I'm sure of it!

Your delusions know no end, do they?
All your faction does is spout hate for
the Other, never stopping to think of
where that hatred stems from.
So long as you continue on that path,\nnothing will ever change.
If you truly seek a future defined by\nhappiness, we must cast the past\naside and write our own future.
Is there really no hope for\nreconciliation...?
Not without change from your side.\nOtherwise, we will keep fighting\nuntil only one faction remains.
That can't be the only way...
I say this as someone who once trained\nalongside you: Don't let your new position\ncloud your judgment.
If you try to wield it like a weapon\nto get what you want, it will cost\nyou your life.
There are many in the Church who do\nnot approve of your appointment.\nIt was not made with pure intentions.
Merely that our beliefs are becoming more\nand more popular within the Churchâ€”and\nthe leadership know it.
So they installed one of their own as\nGrand Paladyn, in hopes of rallying the\npeople to their cause.

You hail from the fallen kingdom of
Alberia, which recognized the Ilian Church
as its official religionâ€”and you now fight
alongside one of its princes.

Beyond that, you're the picture of youth,
strength, and integrityâ€”a recipe
for popularity if ever there was one.
You make for a picturesque Grand Paladyn.
The people will flock to your side, though\nto us, they look like pitiable fools, dancing\nto the tune of liars and frauds.
And what proof do you have of this?!
Why else would Elisanne be chosen\nover such obviously superior candidates?

Still, what's done is doneâ€”and it's
made you very unpopular within the
Church. So I would keep my head down,
if I were youâ€”unless you want to lose it.
I'm fine. I had my own suspicions,\nin truth, but it makes his words\nno less painful.
Still, the role is mine now. There must\nbe some good I can do with it.
(I should be overjoyed at becoming\nGrand Paladyn... So why do I feel\nso empty?)
Why did I become a Paladyn in the\nfirst place...?
Mother, Fatherâ€”I've made up my mind.\nI will become a Paladyn.
Paladyns are protectors, and I want\nto protect everyone.
Not just you and Father, but Alex,\nthe priests, the bishops...
Prayer alone is not enough.\nI can do more. I WILL do more.
I want to protect everyone's happiness.
It's not an easy path, Elisanne; there will\nbe many hard times ahead. Is your dream\nstrong enough to get you through them?
I know it isâ€”I swear it on Ilia's name!
(...I was so naive. And I fear I still\ncan't tell dreams from reality...)
(A shadow has fallen over my path, and it\nonly grows darker with each step I take.)
(And yet still I cling to my dream.\nI want so badly to believe it was\nnot devoid of reality.)
(I want to be the light for those mired in\ndarknessâ€”no matter what I have to lose\nalong the way.)
Those perditionists are gonna pay\nfor what they did to my family!
It seems the perditionists attacked these\npeople without warning. We were too late.
Why does this keep happening...?\nWe all worship the Goddess to find\nhappiness, but...
What's wrong? Can you not find your\nmother?
She prayed to Ilia every day, but she...\n*sniff* She...
(More lives lost to the schism\nwithin the Church...)
(The Grand Paladyn is meant to guide\nthe people...but what path is there out\nof this despair?)
(How can I deliver these people\nfrom darkness?)
